# Apple Notes Gap Roadmap (April 2026)

New roadmap created 2026-04-08 at `roadmap.md` (project root). Replaces the March 2026 roadmap (which was fully completed).

**Why:** User requested a gap analysis against Apple Notes (iOS 26 / macOS 26) to identify missing features and plan sequential implementation.

**How to apply:** Work on one task at a time. Polish each before moving to the next.

## Completed

1. **Complete Markdown Import** (Phase 1) -- added setext headings, indented code blocks, nested blockquote flattening, soft line breaks, bold-italic combos to `NoteImportService.swift`
2. **Web Link Rich Previews** (Phase 1, MVP) -- added "Card" option to URL paste menu. New `[[linkcard|title|desc|url]]` tag with async metadata fetch via `WebMetadataFetcher`. MVP card UI in `LinkCardView` (in `WebClipView.swift`). Ready for UI polish pass.
3. **Quick Notes (Global Hotkey Capture)** (Phase 2, completed 2026-04-09) -- user-configurable global hotkey (default `⌃⇧J`) opens a borderless 600x400 floating `NSPanel` for plain-text capture from any app. Carbon `RegisterEventHotKey` for sandbox-safe registration. Saves to an auto-created "Quick Notes" inbox folder tracked by UUID. Settings recorder surfaces Carbon registration failures inline. New files: `QuickNoteHotKey.swift`, `GlobalHotKeyManager.swift`, `QuickNoteService.swift`, `QuickNotePanel.swift`, `HotKeyRecorderView.swift`. Modified: `ThemeManager.swift` (with `hasFinishedInitialization` flag to fix `@Published` + `didSet` + init bug), `JotApp.swift`, `FloatingSettings.swift`. UI polish pass deferred to a later session per user request.

## Remaining

4. Smart Folders (saved filter predicates)
5. Collapsible Sections (heading-based folding)
6. Map Embedding (MapKit inline attachments)

## Future Exploration (deferred)

- Real-time Collaboration
- Document Scanner
- Widgets (WidgetKit)
- Siri Integration

## Excluded (never)

iCloud Sync, Math Notes, Drawing/Handwriting, Apple Watch
